Description: Alleles found in an individual (or group of individuals).
The sequence corresponding to the seq id, start, end of the associated genomic sequence file.
The effect of a sequence alteration on a sequence feature.
The codons that overlap a feature as modified by the sequences in the Variant_seq attribute.
The codons that overlap a feature on the the reference genome.
The amino acids that overlap a feature as modified by the sequences in the Variant_seq attribute.
The amino acids that overlap a feature on the reference genome.
Describes the source or destination of the a zero-length sequence alteration in the form seqid:start-end:strand.
A region of sequence context from the reference genome around a sequence alteration.
